		<font color="#FFFFFF"><h1>A NOTE FROM MR. JAMIE MITCHELL, SUPERINTENDENT</h1>
		<h3>Gracemont Students and Parents,<br><br>

Your Gracemont teachers, board of education and administration have begun the process to proceed with remote learning for the remainder of our school year. What this means is all education will be completed via electronic or other mediums but not face to face or in standard classroom settings. At the direction of the State Department of Education (SDE), we will prepare an educational plan to provide remote learning to all students. Many of you have questions and I'm sad to say we have no complete answers for the majority of your questions. This journey into remote learning will be an adventure we will all have to work through as we go along. Please remember all information and instructions are subject to change.
<br><br>
What we know:<br>
The school must submit a "Remote Learning Plan" to the SDE for approval.
Remote learning will begin on or before April 6th and continue until the week of May 11-15th. 
You will be contacted by your child(ren)'s teacher(s) to discuss distribution of instructional assignments.
<br><br>
Mr. Mitchell<br>
